						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine of the Tiruvandanāthēśvara temple. </p>						

						<p>On palæographical grounds this fragmentary record may be assigned to the 11th12th centuries.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the <hi rend="italic">tāṉattār</hi> of the temple and mentions a <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇa</hi>, Kāśyapan Āḷuḍaiyāṉ Kāyappāttu Tiruvēṅkaḍa-bhaṭṭan.</p>						

